```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "spockFarm",
    "output_file": "log2-spockFarm-%j.out",
    "partition": "Brody",
    "time_limit": "96:00:00",
    "cores": 1,
    "julia_version": "1.2.0",
    "julia_script": "$1",
    "bspockID": "${SLURM_ARRAY_JOB_ID}_$SLURM_ARRAY_TASK_ID",
    "myRunNumber": "$((SLURM_ARRAY_TASK_ID + taskIDOffset))",
    "hostname": "spock",
    "arguments": "$@",
    "log_file_move": "mv log-array-example-${SLURM_JOB_ID}.out $1/log-array-example-${SLURM_JOB_ID}.out"
  }
}
```

This script uses Slurm for job scheduling and resource management. It runs a Julia script called `$juliaScript` with specific arguments and environment variables. The script utilizes Slurm's job array functionality to run multiple tasks in parallel. It also utilizes a Julia module and moves the log file to a location specified by the input argument.
